Soskic Warns of ‘Risks’ in Meeting Terms of IMF Loan, Beta Says

-- B y   M i s h a   S a v i c
-- 
2011-09-02T15:14:49Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-09-02/soskic-warns-of-risks-in-meeting-terms-of-imf-loan-beta-says.html
Serbia  faces “certain risks” in
meeting the conditions of its 1 billion-euro ($1.42 billion)
arrangement with the  International Monetary Fund ,  Beta   news
agency  reported, citing central bank Governor Dejan Soskic.  The “biggest challenges” include a required cut in state
spending and implementing structural reforms in Serbia’s public
sector, the newswire quoted Soskic as saying in an interview
today.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Misha Savic in Belgrade at 
 msavic2@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
